

= [[Green Computing]] coordination project proposed by the [[Open Grid Forum]]


=Description=

Craig Lee:

"The basic concept of the Green VM project
is to coordinate existing green IT projects that are grid/cloud/
virtualization-related and maximize their visibility and impact.
Green IT essentially requires a monitoring system for energy
consumption whose information can be used to direct system behavior
and enforce energy policy.  Besides monitoring server electrical
consumption, cooling energy consumption can also be monitored.
Decision tools can then direct effectors, such as the initial
placement or migration of VMs, or powering servers up or down.
Current projects that have been in discussion are OpenNebula (UCM),
Reservoir (EU), Green-Net (INRIA/Lyon), and Low Carbon ICT (Oxford).
The GreenLight project from CalIT2 is another possibility.  The goal
here is to coordinate existing work, possibly around a reference model
for green IT that clearly identifies areas for best practices and
possible standards.  This effort should be coordinated with other
groups such as GreenGrid.org and ClimateSaversComputing.org.  We
should also coordinate with the EU wrt the EU Data Centre Code of
Conduct."
(Arch-econ mailing list, 9/2008)



